          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "PHD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The  energy  separation of the protons and",
                " deuterons  from  He-3  was  achieved  by  pulseshape",
                " discrimination.   Number  of  silicon detectors with",
                " depletion depths ranging from 0.045 to 3.0  mm  were",
                " used  either  singly  or  in  combinations of two to",
                " separate protons and deuterons from  the  background",
                " due to electrons and neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target  consisted  of  two  similar gas cells 1.5",
                " inches in diameter by  2  inches  in  length,  which",
                " could  be  moved  in  and  out of the beam by remote",
                " control.  One cell was fitted with  a  0.00025  inch",
                " havar  window  at  90 degrees t0 the beam and filled",
                " with 3 atm of H-2.  The other cell had mylar windows",
                " of  either 0.00014 or 0.00050 inches filled with 0.5",
                " and 1.33 atm,  respectively,  of He-3. Both the He-2",
                " and He-3 gases were to be better than 99.5% pure."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A  number  of  silicon  detectors  with",
                " depletion depths ranging from 0.045 to 3.0 mm placed",
                " in focal plane of a quadrupole-triplet magnet."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The deuteron  energy  spectra  were measured for some",
                " runs.  The total number  of  deuteron  counts  in  a",
                " spectrum   peak   at  each  run  was  determined  by",
                " substracting the background obtained in a  run  with",
                " an  evacuated  target cell and the quadrupole magnet",
                " at a similar field  setting.  The  total  number  of",
                " deuteron  counts  from  He-3  contained  in  a  peak",
                " together  with the total  number  of  proton  counts",
                " from  He-2  contained in a peak produced by the same",
                " gamma  energy  and  with  the  Deswart  and  Marshak",
                " theoretical  cross section d-sig/d-omega (H-2) at 90",
                " degrees in the laboratory system were used to obtain",
                " the   differential   cross   section  for  He-3(g,d)",
                " reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "R",
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": "J.J.De Swart+",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,PHY,25,1001,1959",
                  "field": {
                    "reference_type": "J",
                    "reference": {
                      "code": "PHY",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "25",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "1001"
                    },
                    "date": 1959
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "     Theoretical",
                " differential  cross   section   for   the   H-2(g,p)",
                " reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The He-3(g,d)p  differential  cross  section  at   90",
                " degrees  in  the laboratory system has been measured",
                " in the gamma-ray energy range of 8.5 to  46  MeV.  A",
                " broad  peak  with a maximum of 93 microbarn/sr at 11",
                " mev  is  observed.  The  He-3(g,2p)n  proton  energy",
                " spectrum  produced by 40 MeV bremsstrahlung has also",
                " been measured.  A survey of sum-rule predictions  is",
                " also included."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
